            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A knowledge panel is an information box Google displays on the right side of desktop search results (or at the top on mobile) when it confidently identifies the entity behind a search. It shows facts like a business's hours, location, description, logo, and social links — pulled from Google's Knowledge Graph.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I get a knowledge panel for my business?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Start with a verified Google Business Profile, Organization schema on your website with sameAs links, and consistent business information across authoritative directories. A Wikidata entry significantly increases your chances. Wikipedia is not required but accelerates the process considerably.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I edit my knowledge panel?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>After claiming your panel via Google Search Console, you can suggest edits to the description, images, and social profile links. Google reviews all suggested changes before applying them. Factual claims require verifiable sources before Google will accept them.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Why did my knowledge panel disappear?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Panels disappear when Google loses confidence in entity data — often from conflicting information across sources, a Wikipedia article being deleted, schema markup removed after a site rebuild, or a Google Business Profile being suspended. Audit all entity signals and rebuild the ones that broke.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does a knowledge panel affect SEO rankings?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Not directly as an organic ranking factor. But a knowledge panel dominates your branded SERP, boosts click-through rates by approximately 30%, and signals to Google that your entity is well-understood — which can indirectly improve topical authority and AI Overview citation frequency.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

